buildRequest

public HttpRequest buildRequest(java.lang.String fullyQualifiedMethodName,
                                java.lang.Object parameters)
                         throws java.io.IOException
Creates an HTTP request based on the given method name and parameters.

If the discovery document has not yet been loaded, it will call load().

Parameters:
fullyQualifiedMethodName - name of method as defined in Discovery document of format "resourceName.methodName"
parameters - user defined key / value data mapping or null for none
Returns:
HTTP request
Throws:
java.io.IOException - I/O exception reading
